    "text": "FtMYB13, a R2R3-MYB from Tartary buckwheat, is located in the nucleus and is not a transcriptional activator. Compared to wild type (WT), transgenic Arabidopsis overexpressing FtMYB13 showed lower ABA sensitivity and improved drought/salt tolerance. This was due to higher proline content, greater photosynthetic efficiency, higher transcript abundance of stress-related genes, and smaller amounts of reactive oxygen species (ROS) and malondialdehyde (MDA).",
